Combination Air/Sea Trips
PAL passengers may now enjoy both the speed of air travel
and the fascination of life aboard ship on trans-Pacific trips.
By agreement with American President Lines, tickets for a
combination air/sea voyage may be purchased at fares
equal to one-half the applicable round trip fares between
the point of embarkation and point of debarkation on each
carrier.

World Travelers
choose
PHILIPPINE AIR LINES
BATAAN
for:
* Proved Dependability
of its luxurious Douglas DC-6's and skilled, experienced
flight crews. Known and respected throughout the world,
the famed four-engined DC-6 has earned an unequaled
reputation for comfort and dependability in air travel.
P.A.L.'s experienced flight crews, personalized service
and trained cabin attendants are your assurance of a
perfect trip.
* Unexcelled Service
provided by courteous, competent pursers and cabin
attendants. Excellent hot meals, refreshing between-meal
snacks and the sincere desire to make your flight a thor-
oughly enjoyable experience explain why world travelers
acclaim the friendly, personalized service of Philippine
Air Lines.
* Real Comfort
of the DC-6 pressurized, air-conditioned cabin —its adjust-
able reclining chairs, full-size sleeping berths and con-
venient lounges. Smooth,
"above-weather" flight along
P.A.L's sunny route is your assurance of comfortable
travel in any season.
* Fast, Reliable Schedules
made possible by dependable 300-mile-per-hour DC-6's
and P.A.L.'s direct routes around 2/3 of the world. On-
time departures and arrivals and minimum stopovers have
made the Route of the Orient Star one of the world's
fastest and most reliable.
